## Finding: No Internationalization (i18n) Implementation Skill

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: MEDIUM
### Evidence: Zero coverage of i18n/L10n in any Phase 3 skill. frontend_patterns covers accessibility but not i18n. api_design has no mention of locale-aware API design (Accept-Language headers, locale parameters). For any application serving international users, i18n is a build-time concern: strings must be externalized from day one, date/number/currency formatting must use locale-aware libraries, right-to-left (RTL) layout must be considered, and the backend must support locale-specific data.
### Proposed Resolution: New skill `internationalization` in Phase 3. Scope: React i18next setup, translation key management, locale-aware formatting (Intl API), NestJS i18n module, RTL CSS considerations, and the build pipeline impact of translation file management.
### Cross-Phase Impact: Phase 2 (design must specify target locales), Phase 4 (locale-specific test cases), Phase 5 (deployment must serve correct locale assets), Phase 6 (handoff must document translation workflow).

