## Finding: Build Order Recommendation — Proposed Skill Sequencing

### Gap Type: MISSING_SKILL
### Severity: CRITICAL
### Evidence: Dependency analysis above reveals a required build order for proposed skills. Attempting to teach resiliency_patterns before event_driven_architecture, or privacy_by_design before authorization_patterns, creates forward references and incomplete understanding.
### Proposed Resolution:

WAVE 1 — Foundation extensions (no new skills, extend existing):
1. api_design Part 15: Swagger/OpenAPI (S, 1-2 hrs) — standalone edit
2. auth_implementation Part 8: Security Headers (S, 1-2 hrs) — standalone edit
3. observability Part 11: OpenTelemetry (M, half-day) — standalone edit

WAVE 2 — New P0/P1 standalone skills (no interdependencies):
4. test_driven_build (M, half-day) — P0 CRITICAL, do first
5. dependency_hygiene (S, 1-2 hrs) — P1, quick win
6. secret_management (M, half-day) — P1
7. backward_compatibility (M, half-day) — P1
8. authorization_patterns (M, half-day) — P1

WAVE 3 — New P1/P2 skills with dependencies:
9. feature_flags (M, half-day) — depends on Wave 2 completion
10. privacy_by_design (M, half-day) — depends on authorization_patterns
11. event_driven_architecture (L, full-day) — foundational for Wave 4

WAVE 4 — Skills depending on Wave 3:
12. resiliency_patterns (L, full-day) — depends on event_driven_architecture
13. realtime_patterns (M, half-day) — depends on event_driven_architecture
14. state_machine_patterns (M, half-day) — independent but better after event-driven

WAVE 5 — P2/P3 skills (lower priority):
15. i18n / internationalization (M)
16. IaC (L, full-day)
17. enterprise_sso (M)
18. monorepo_patterns (M)
19. graphql_patterns (L)
20. code_generation (M)
21. SLO/error budgets (S, extension to observability)
22. SSRF/injection defense (S, extension to backend_patterns)
23. SBOM (S, extension to docker_development)
24. implementation_sequencing (M, new skill)
25. build_reproducibility (M, new skill)

### Cross-Phase Impact: Executing skills in this order ensures no forward references. Wave 1 can begin immediately. Wave 2 requires no infrastructure. Wave 3+ require Redis (Docker Compose already in docker_development).

